I am out today. How about another day?
Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.
Sure, I will wait for you at home.
Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

dru: ikɨbobaro técavɨnali si ipasɨksɨktɨlakɨ tsɨkɨla, adradria.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.
Thank you for accepting the interview.
You are welcome. What would you like to know?
What do you do when you are young?
I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

dru: ko vlakɨso ka. iké ckɨlɨmo sɨdanɨ
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?
No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

dru: othɨdekɨ sesana atho si sesana raramɨ, thɨkadanɨlii kidri.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

dru: othɨdekɨ ngɨsa ngiyo, ikédra tapɨra kwa ka ikɨthaingongokɨkɨ
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.
I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

dru: ikadroarigwali makɨsi arigoali ka nobrimakɨswa tilila
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.
Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?
Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.

dru: si bébibé ka odoro kɨsapara olopo?
english: Then, can women go hunting together?
No, women cannot go hunting either.
Kanao, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.
There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!
One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.
I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?
Yes! How many bottles do you need?
I want two bottles and a pack of rice.
Here is the rice, what else do you need?
I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?
I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.
Please give me the clothes in blue.
Kanao, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?
No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

dru: tomédria, ikésoasamoro ngiobonga? tangodrosa mwa koenɨ.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?
No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.
Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?
The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?
Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

dru: borakoa ngidrosoaɨbɨkɨ na lcenge si sesatngitngi na porathi.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

dru: Arase maimorokɨkɨ emcɨ ngipico, dromamoso psédemekwa
english: Arase, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?
I don't have one either. This is Mrinu's.

dru: doroma moso psédɨmekwala sɨpéliakɨ si kosɨvéréswa
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.
Thank you and thank Mrinu for me.
I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?
I would like to borrow these three books.
Sure and remember to return them after three days.
You haven't returned me the eraser.
Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to Mrinona?
I don't know. I will go and ask her.
I will lend you my eraser first.

dru: Mrino kɨné ɨbɨlɨ ka pakésdemani swa Arasɨ?
english: Mrino, did Arasɨ lend you this coat?
No, my mom bought it for me.
Arasɨ's coat is the same as yours.
His coat is black, so our colors are different.
Mrino, did you borrow money from Arasa?

dru: iyo, tlonɨli ka sesa kosvérédri makɨ maimorokɨ ɨngmcɨ péso.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.
Okay, I will tell Arasa for you.

dru: matɨkadrɨngé na poréta tmothoa ka tengnɨ poréta tokoesɨ ka orithi
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.
No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

dru: si kopropro swa tomanɨni pétha kɨné drodrosa sraké tengnɨ si saritha
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

dru: iyo! skargi! toménidria ka dromangakɨ porabɨrɨ.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

dru: tongmaka dadradronga na sɨro mowa tsɨkɨla mɨra na tɨkoko twa tongma.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

dru: iké tingapa bila mɨdanɨ so tsɨkɨla ka cngɨlɨmamɨso
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

dru: cngɨla mɨréso mtolanga moso magɨrangɨ tɨkoko.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.
My trap is under that tree.
This is my hunting zone, so I know where my trap is.
This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

dru: tédranɨma orongo, srakéknamɨ sɨnagɨnagɨpia nogɨpi akangɨ.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

dru: israkailakɨ na sɨnagɨpia sɨkakolanɨnga ka boborakoani?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?

dru: iyo! sɨkakolanɨnga ka tangodrosa moa nogɨnagɨpi.
english: Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

dru: si sɨkakolanɨnga ka koproprosoa pétha orongo.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

dru: avlɨvlɨ nɨgépso nonagɨpiaa kangɨ ibonga blibili.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

dru: adrala, aviɨviɨ avangɨ, kokékɨné plipili sɨnagɨpia moakɨdro psoprakwa mɨra rɨvathɨ.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

dru: mɨra akangɨ blibili pavéthakwa kopsopraswa blibili.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

dru: sɨkragi! madro arata sesa pasɨtɨmiti sɨporo.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.
Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.

dru: adra imililivinga, ibonga inono iké ténonoaso.
english: Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

dru: kingyobi sesa, tébarbarvia kosianga, tangoresɨ mobalte moa mililivi ni!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

dru: soiyobi kosianga, twa milili babangɨ na kosianga ni!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!
What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

dru: niciobi na kosianga, nongoresɨ ma kɨkɨ ninana moa kiokai.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.

dru: api tota koa, noama kɨkɨ bénzio.
english: I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.

dru: singsé, otrɨtrɨ brangɨli, noama kɨkɨ bénzio.
english: Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.
May I go wash my hands?

dru: no siake manga, adrala si lasa wa.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

dru: singsé, otrɨtrɨ oroli, no barvi ma kɨkɨ vévanɨnga.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

dru: singsé, skacɨyobinga ka no barvi ma kɨkɨ mwa pcɨngɨlɨ na koisanga.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.
She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

dru: otrɨtrɨ toloréni ko Kanao, ébrévé sesa.
english: Teacher, Kanau has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

dru: Lola kɨkɨ, cacvélé ka makmangsalɨ cvélli.
english: My name is Lola, and I'm 10 years old.
What ethnic group are you from?
Are all your family members indigenous?
Yes, my whole family is Rukai.

dru: éni, mama ka Drokaizoko, nina ka Pikisia.
english: No, my father is Rukai, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.

dru: mamimoa kdroo? pidra nga ko cvélni?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

dru: éni, ckɨlɨ namɨ ko maodrangɨ kini, mvarlonga ko cvélni.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

dru: cvélni kakimoa sovlé ka tradro la swa ngiadronga?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

dru: cvélni kakasovlé ka tradro la kwa klrima.
skaragreli ka sessa na ɨdé si mthéptele.
médavli ipcacɨnglata nga, tradronga moso yo?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

dru: iyo, skatradroli ka sessa na ɨdé si motolrolo nga.
iyo, knénga ko skadɨkrɨli ka motolrolo nga.

english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

dru: iké tolongolongɨra, nospélia si makɨla ma longolongé.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

dru: ikadra Aroy? nospélia si no makɨla mana opidipdakɨ.
english: Where is Aruy? She's going to compete in a running competition later.
She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

dru: kowa thiorola moa longé kdrali, adrala si kwa silpe swa.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

dru: moa silpe na ico, noa ma kɨkɨ silpe singsé na.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

dru: makɨla ma sesa Ubakɨ na sokongkongo babangɨ?
english: Is Ubakɨ competing in croquet today?

dru: éni, no makɨla ma na oroboboelɨ maragrɨ.
english: No, he's competing in high jump.

dru: ondonkai dria ko vienɨ nomakɨla ma moso?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

dru: iyo, nomakɨla ma kɨkɨ na opdipdakɨ.
nomakɨla ma kɨkɨ na sokongkongo babange.

english: What will we do in the sports day?

dru: nomakɨla ma miti na mabablibli tési.
english: We will compete in tug of war.

dru: ondonkai ka nolɨngalɨngé ma miti na akankana?
english: Will we sell food at the sports day?

dru: éni, nolɨngalɨngé ma miti na babangɨ.
amara moso na iciban yo, makɨcɨngɨ moso!
english: Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.

dru: ikai, mobolɨtɨla, ngiyobonga ka losa siviri.
english: No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

dru: iké danɨ garɨ, moa mbɨlɨngɨ silpe nia!
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

dru: Ubakɨ yo, médavlinga ko icɨngɨlali swa, margi moso?
english: It's Ubakɨ. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?

dru: margi kɨkɨ! mokanikɨ silpe swa modradrɨke.
english: I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.

dru: iké tkankana tlacɨnge, kwa koko nia.
english: He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.
She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

dru: ikai danɨ ki momomoa, iké toma, drodrovadri moa siviridranga iké danɨ.!
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.

dru: médavli nga ipcacɨngɨla ta, maragre nga moso.
english: I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.

dru: cɨnglɨ madɨ taknianɨso ka mbebere ko kdrɨdrɨmɨ madɨ.
english: It's so good to see you.

dru: sbénɨme moa kné pongodrɨle, apoa madɨ podringi pingsiang.
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

dru: médavlinga ikwaniaso, nanga kiania samia mokné ngoresɨ koenɨ.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

dru: adra ikopongo, nongolo mili na ocia si mekɨtɨnga, nanga si takédanɨ modradrɨkɨ.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.

dru: takdrɨngéso tormana kwa, nosiviri manga kɨkɨ.
english: Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

dru: kirolathɨ la kné toroka, mra omcɨ pisiviri ngitikii koenɨ.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.
Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?

dru: také mdradrɨsngɨ gakko ni? ta poéga.
english: How about meeting at school? We need to shoot a video.

dru: twa tsorsorbwane miso, noslabingi ma kɨkɨ moa.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

dru: ckɨckɨlɨ namɨ pohanéni sakora ka sakora na margi. tadro na pohanéninga ka mokonia silpekwa ni!
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!

dru: toménidria ka noa manga na klatingingisanɨ, médavlingaa!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Then come during our Harvest Festival!
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!

dru: kola swa koboboro nogɨne sivirisonga moa ckɨckɨlɨ?
english: May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.

dru: nakoso ikai ldreke pikisia boboro solosolote?
english: Why not teach in the city?

dru: mathrébo kwa ko ckɨckɨlɨli, smarnga ladoro kɨkɨ siviri posopra ckɨckɨlɨ mia.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

dru: orogo moso nonoro, aci ko oboroboro swa?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

dru: amani ko kakorongonɨma, amani origonga nonoro ko ckɨckɨlɨ namɨ.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.
How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

dru: nonoro ka bonkanɨme kini, nipocongocongolo bonkanɨme ma kɨkɨ.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.

dru: kné kbava bcɨngɨ matkadrɨngé margi ongolo madɨ.
skakɨcɨngɨ moso, médavlɨ na zikan tbavémadɨ?
english: You're really talented. Does it take a long time to make?

dru: éni, noama na icingci si mekɨtɨnga. thioro la madɨ coloko ptido bcɨngɨ, lapwa satbavne nono ptaresɨ, si podringinga ko mkedrɨsa cɨbakɨ.
english: No, it only takes about a week. After steaming the sticky rice and white rice, we mix it with yeast powder, and then it can be stored in a jar.

dru: iké kwa kné na tngavlo si lcenge na lokio, angidokali samia!
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

dru: nolngé ma knia drosa lcenge, pidra?
ngicolo ka drosa ɨdé si mlrémle na péso.
madlamɨ kwa nia kné mamɨne, pidra?
english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?

dru: kné mamɨne ka lrima ɨdé na péso.
makcɨngénga sakora, doria pitimrɨ ngitiki la?
english: It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?
No, if I lower it further, I'll lose money.

dru: iyo mso! kolɨngé ngɨsa tmacɨcrɨngɨ na mamɨne.
english: Alright then, I'll take a black piece of clothing.

dru: nolɨngé ma kɨkɨ nia kné saldro si plongo.
english: I want this knife and this pot.

dru: ngicolo ka drosa kozolo na péso, angipéthali kini, nodoro ma madɨ asarké médavli na zikang.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

dru: kosiokai lséli si lalili nanga longia mia, doro ma moso pitimɨrɨ ngitiki la?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?

dru: iyo iyo, ko pirimrɨ soa poa pace mia.
english: Alright! I'll give you a 20% discount.

dru: nanga cɨngcɨngla! iké alanglangranɨme na mamɨne si toropongo.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

dru: sessa na mamɨne ka tolro ɨdé si mlrémle na péso, tolro mamɨne ka sessa na kozolo péso.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

dru: lngé ma kɨkɨ ngɨsa na mamɨne si mekɨtɨnga, borakwa na bovanɨ la.
english: I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

dru: margi moso, apilɨngé kwa vilitoro naboro si tékananɨ na makao botolo.
english: Hello, I would like to buy sticky rice and braised pork with maqaw pepper.

dru: kélɨngé ngicolonga boro. ikéla kwa na potngarvanɨ na ténpora, nolɨngé ma moso?
english: The rice is sold out. I have tana pancakes, would you like to buy them?

dru: nakoni! borakwa ngɨsa, mokonélinga na skakolanɨ ka kolngé na boro.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

dru: iyo, koposoprasoa bothobongo, toménia ka mlrémle na péso.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

dru: saabaw makanaelre. kaykameane lri bolroa ko mitaane kay taleke ngkay ki Ngodradrekadhane swaveavedadhane.
english: Hello everyone. Today, I am going to teach you how to speak the Wutai Rukai language for food.

dru: poalringalringaw so kay vaga ki sinsi?
english: Do you understand what the teacher says?

dru: sinsi, kainako poalringalringaw. lri maka pelana so kawriva?
english: I don't understand. Can you repeat it again?

dru: kainako maka kialalra, lri maka akoadrawana so?
english: I can't hear you, can you speak louder?

dru: ala dreela papia kay! topaapalra ili kingivale silrigo.
english: Look here, please! Repeat after me.
Read it again. Please speak louder.

dru: sinsi, marimora ko iloko ko sapacapacasane.
english: I forgot to bring my pen.

dru: sinsi, marimora ko iloko ko sasopisopilrane.
english: I forgot to bring my eraser.

dru: ala kisalroana ki papalra so ko sasopisopilrane.
english: Please borrow erasers from your classmates.

dru: pakeakela ta kikay kaykameane, tamadreedrelenga lokabiibilrili ki amakapitolane.
english: Class dismissed, see you next week.

dru: lalaka ko ki palripilripi, sia Kaynwana ko.
english: I am the son of Palripilripi, my name is Kaynwane.

dru: sitoa ko ki Aropo, sia Cangala ko.
english: I'm a student at Arupu, my name is Cangale.

dru: sia aneane ko nagane ki tama so?
ko nagane ki ama sia Cangale.

english: He is my brother, his name is Kalrimadraw.

dru: sia aneane ko nagane ki laso?
ko nagane ki lasoso sia Paidrisi?
oono, sia Paidrisi ko nagne ki laso.
sia Takanaw ko nagane ki laso?
ini, ko nagane ini sia Kocilro.
ka aliso sia Laloi,ina ka betakane ki ina.
kavay aliso laali ili, sia Legeane ko nagane ini.
english: She's a friend of mine and her name is Legeane.

dru: tarapinga ko caili ki tama so?

english: How many brothers and sisters do you have?

dru: tadrosa ko kaka ka sawvalay si ababay, tangea ko agili ka ababay.
english: I have two brothers and sisters and one younger brother and sister.
How many people are in your family?
There are four of us in our family.

dru: manemane ko aongane ki tama so ka betakane ki tina so?
english: What does your uncle do for a living?

dru: yakay ko aongane ki taka ka ababay?
english: Does your sister have a job?
Yes, I'm from the Rukai tribe.
Yes, but she's from the Taroko tribe.
Yes, we are all very tall.
Does your sister go to school?

dru: ko laagi ka sawvalay wathimgale ki vaga nomi?
english: Do your siblings speak the language?
Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
I have three brothers and sisters.

dru: taelre so ki tama so si tina so.
english: Do you live with your parents?

dru: ono, taelrea ko ki ama si ina.
english: Yes, I live with my mom and dad.

dru: taerle so ki tomo so si kayngo so?
english: Do you live with your grandparents?
No, I didn't live with them.

dru: taelrea ko ki ama, ina, kaka kasawvalay.
english: I live with my father, mother and brother.
When are you going back to the tribe?

dru: loka taibalribalrivane ki kaladralrangedrangane tara moabalriva ko.
english: I will go back in the summer.
The sun is coming out, it's very hot.
Is it going to be cold outside?
It's cold, so wear more clothes.
It's neither cold nor hot today, very comfortable.

dru: kadro ko emeeme belenge, ngiaboalenga ka latariaw.
english: There were no clouds in the sky; the stars came out.

dru: tawcekaceka ko odale, ngiaboalenga ka vai, labalrilaolawnga.
english: The rain has just stopped, the sun has come out, the rainbow is coming out.

dru: ngitoatomane ko talikay mosoane ko saseverane?
english: What's the weather like where you are?
We're going to have a big storm here.
Very well, out of the big sun.
I have to go to school.
The weather is very cold, so wear more clothes.

dru: lri odale loasane, ngolringava iloko ko lenay.
english: It's going to rain heavily, you have to remember to bring an umbrella.
There was thunder just now, and it's supposed to rain later.
It just rained, and now it's stopped.
It seems to have rained and the road is wet.
Is it raining? Why are you all wet?

dru: waodaodale latadre, kainako wailoko ko lenay.
english: It's raining outside, so I didn't bring an umbrella.

dru: maadraw ko valrigi, macaeme kay aolro li ki takovalrigane.
english: The wind is blowing so hard that my head hurts.

dru: maadraw kay vai, pakabithengelre ki aolro li.
english: The sun is so big, it makes me dizzy.
I forgot to bring my pen.
I forgot to bring my chopsticks.
I don't have one either, let's go buy one.
Let's go buy a pen, shall we?
Well, I still have to buy erasers.
Let's go get breakfast, shall we?
No, I've already eaten at home.

dru: marimora ko palaw ko laolri ili.
english: I forgot to steam my lunchbox.
I forgot to bring my lunchbox.
Then let's eat my lunch box together!
What are you having for lunch?

dru: lri kanea ko ko kodrali ki gako.
english: I want a nutritious school lunch.
What are you having for lunch?

dru: kaykameane! wailokako kay binto! tatadrosanga tokodrali!
english: I've brought a lunchbox today, let's eat together at noon!
Let's go play basketball, shall we?
Please help me with the broom.
Okay, here's a broomstick for you.
Can you help me with the cloth?
I'm sweeping the floor and you asked Kalange to help you.
The floor is dirty, go clean it.
Okay, I'll go get the cloth.
That window is very dirty, go clean it.
Wait a minute, I'm not done sweeping here yet.

dru: Ngoa kisia ngoa ngiapalay so moa Taito?
english: Are you going to Taitung by train or by plane?

dru: Ngoa ngiapaladha ko, mariaridare ki kisia ngokay ki ngiapalay.
english: I will take the plane because it is faster than the train.

dru: Lo moa so kikway ngobaase ngiaongotingi so?
english: Are you going to drive to the church or take the bus?

dru: Ngia ongotinga ko moa kiwkay, masolialivate ki baase ngiaongotingi.
english: I will drive to the church because it is more convenient than the bus.
Is the market close to your house?
No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.
Is the post office close to the school?

dru: Adeethe, tinoa daadavace mado si moa.
english: Yes, it is within walking distance.
Is the restaurant close to the station?

dru: Sana molatadrane tisiaba daadavace ka lrima pongokange si daroro.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.
I would like to visit you.

dru: Yakay ko aongane li kainako lri itavanane. Lokakaiyaiyanga.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

dru: Loiya yakay ko zikange so? Naw kelanga lomakomolringedele.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.
Sure, I will wait for you at home.

dru: Lri maka bilibila ko? Naw pacase amia ko.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

dru: Kainako matahriri, lakaika nilripethelane ka taseketane, palrainga.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.

dru: Maelanenga lapakela so nakoane lrikape mosoane.
english: Thank you for accepting the interview.

dru: Kaimatoamen, lri kivavaa so ko manemane?
english: You are welcome. What would you like to know?
What do you do when you are young?
I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

dru: Ko lalake so mialri ikaykay cekele?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?

dru: Ini, ko lalakeli yakay cekele talidratane.
english: No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

dru: Yakay ko lapolapoli ko vaeva ko taopongo si vaeva ka adhaadhame, mialri lini ka wacekecekele li.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

dru: Mialri lapoa ko ko vaeva ko ngiaw, laikay kay lawaodriodripi kaido tasepele.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

dru: Naw kiavavaga ko ngoakay ki nitotaolrisiane ki waalopo.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

dru: Kaika thainiino ko thingale li, ai ko amaka tobalreane li lritara tobalrea ko mosoane.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.

dru: Ko rarokorokodro ki waalopo manemane ko nitotaolrisiane?
english: Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?

dru: Ko saaloalopane kaimaka solrape ko labaibay.
english: Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.

dru: Kavay ababay lri maka topalra alopo?
english: Then, can women go hunting together?
No, women cannot go hunting either.

dru: Karaosane, kadronga ko masikaw, lolangadha ko masikaw.
english: Karausane, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.

dru: Yakayyana ko akovaevanga ikay taagaagane, asilangayana!
english: There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!
One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

dru: Lrl langadhako ko masikaw, kialangalangay nomi?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?
Yes! How many bottles do you need?

dru: Lri ngoakodrosa ko langay, si akovaeva ki lomase ko pagay.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.

dru: Yakay kay pagay, manemaneana ko morikay so?
english: Here is the rice, what else do you need?

dru: Lri langadhako ko batoko, yakay nomianane?
english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

dru: Lri langadhako ko edreedrekane ko alrimane.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.

dru: Yakay ka lraolarpongo si saleseese nay.
english: We have white and blue ones too.

dru: Ala baadhaili ko saleseese ko laimay.
english: Please give me the clothes in blue.

dru: Kalrasingane moaino so koasane? Waongodo so?
english: Kalrasingane, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

dru: Ini, paraloba ko ki kaingo langay ko lacenge.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

dru: Iya, yakay ko zikange so lomaongo? lrikela so kibalrolo nakoane.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?

dru: Ini, lri langadha ko ko laimay.
english: No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

dru: Saabaw, kikay ereerece kay lacenge twapiapia?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

dru: Ko ereerece ko lacenge maposale ka balrolane.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?

dru: Kay vorasi ko vaeva kingi matolrolo ka balrolane.
english: Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

dru: Ala baadhaili ko drosa ka ereerece ko lacenge si vaeva kingi ka vorasi.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

dru: Koi, marimora ko ko sapacapacasane, lri maka pakisaalroanana so nakoane?
english: Kui, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?
I don't have one either. This is Paduay's.

dru: Lai pakisaalro so nakoane padalroana? Lri padalroako si saolri mosoane.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.
Thank you and thank Pidhuay for me.

dru: Lri saolria ko kay drosa kay hongo.
english: I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?

dru: Lri kisaalroana nako ko tolro ko hongo.
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

dru: Mathariringa. tarangolringava si kela saolri lomakatolrolonga.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

dru: Kai so wasaolriana ko sasopisopilrane li.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.
Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to Kalravuane?

dru: Kai nako wathingale. Lo kivaga ki aliso.
english: I don't know. I will go and ask her.
I will lend you my eraser first.

dru: Pangodrale, kikay sapakabelengane pakisaalro mosane ki Karoko?
english: Pangudrale, did Karuku lend you this coat?

dru: Ini, kikay langay ki ina si baai nakoane.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

dru: Ka sapakabelengane ki Karoko maramaw ki mosoane.
english: Karuku's coat is the same as yours.

dru: Ka sapakabelengane ki laso iceecelrenge, makaela ko kolaw nay.
english: His coat is black, so our colors are different.

dru: Pelelresane, kiasaalro so ki Kolele ko payso?
english: Pelelresane, did you borrow money from Kulele?

dru: Uno, nayka wasaolria ko iniane kaykameane, kainako siapayso.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.
Okay, I will tell Kulele for you.

dru: Kay ciici arakay ko takebe tokolro, kay tikoray arakay ko dringay, pacengecenge pia kikay.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

dru: Anika pangimia kikay, tapasamaliane li! Tharepane kakadroa ko makapoalraalra.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

dru: Naw bolroana mosoane darepe kikay drosa ka satokotokolrane.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

dru: Mathariri! ala mathariri toramoro! lobiibilrili lrimaka poalranga ko labolabolay.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

dru: Maelrengenga ka obolo angaangade, lo moa taseketane malra ko takaokaw, ila tangodalrane.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

dru: Yakay ki thiili ki cepenge ki tapavaivaiyane ki taleke, sana modaane so ki taseketane lri dreele so.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

dru: Drareela malra, madha kadoladola. Marangisi toramoro kwini takaokaw.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

dru: Ko tokolro li yatailebe kavay ki angato.
english: My trap is under that tree.

dru: Patoathingala ko pikay kikay, wathingala ko ka yatalikay ino ko tokolro li.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

dru: Kikay romoko, pikay nay ki babiabila ki drakerale si poromokane ki kaange.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

dru: Kadroa ko romoko nay kay, arakay nay ko salrakoikoilane tokaange.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

dru: Kai nako arakayyana ko salrakoikoilane, lobiibilrili bolroangaili midra?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?
Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

dru: Naw bolronga mosoane ko tadaredarepane ko romoko ki kaange.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

dru: Ngiavevele kwini salrakoikoilane so, alaw moakailanenga ko kaange! kirimoa malra bilibili.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

dru: Idrengerana, walokalokay toramoro kay varokoro. Naw sakay kay kikay bilibili.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

dru: Malra bilibili papia nakoane. Naw paralobo mosoane bilibili.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

dru: Ala mathariri toramoro! pangiaesay kaykameane, soaeteane kay romoko ki kaange.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.

dru: Ila takirarimo mobalriw si pangisabolo mitaane.
english: Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.

dru: Kaykameane lri bolroa ko nomiane ki lawaodriodripi Ngodradreadrekadhane.
english: I will teach everyone all kinds of animals in Ngudradrekay language today.

dru: Kaykameane lri bolroa ko nomiane ki lamadro ki angato Ngodradreadrekadhane.
english: I will teach everyone all kinds of fruits in Ngudradrekay language today.
Teacher, I didn't bring my textbook.
Share the book with your classmate next to you.
I will lend you my eraser.
It is the end of the class, be careful on your way home.
The class is over, goodbye everyone.

dru: Saabaw makanaelre, ko nagane li sia Cangale.
english: Hello everyone, my name is Cangale.

dru: Saabw makanaelre, ko nagane li sia Aropo.
english: Hello everyone, my name is Arupu.

dru: Agiako ki Ivay, ko nagane li sia Avoso.
english: I am Ivay's sister. My name is Avusu.

dru: Sinisi li ki laso, sia Lomane.
Ka laso kaka, ka laso sia Kakoromane.
Sianeane ko nagane ki taka ka ababay?
english: What is your elder sister's name?

dru: Ko nagane ki kaka sia Avoso.
english: My elder sister's name is Avusu.

dru: Siaanena ko angane ki agi ka ababay?
english: What is your younger sister's name?

dru: Sia Pelrese ko nagane ki agili ka ababay.
english: My younger sister's name is Pelrese.

dru: Wathingale so ko nagane ki laso?
Tarapianga ko caili ki taka ka sawvalay kaiciali?
english: How old is your elder brother?

dru: Tarapianga ko caili ki agi ka sawvalay kaicaili?
english: How old is your younger brother?

dru: Yakay ko gako ki cekele nomi?
english: Do you have schools in your community?
Do you study in your tribe's school?

dru: Uno, ikay nay gako mia nay ki wacekecekele.
english: Yes, we are like family while we are studying at school.

dru: Madha kivavavangeana, Kirimoa moa ki taetale nene.
english: Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

dru: Kaykameane Kingi ka Vai, loiya tatelradhane, ila tamolatadre kivaavange!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

dru: Loiya Acilay ka Vai, loiya tangimalri!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!

dru: Loiya lomiamialre manemane ko atomanane so?
english: What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

dru: Loiya Vai ki Vai, konako si ina lri mokiwkay nay.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.
Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.
May I go wash my hands?

dru: Lripadalronga si paalikay kay takibolroane, idrengerana.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

dru: Sinisi lrikivagako loka Vai ki Dramare, lrikisolravako.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.
She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

dru: Sinisi, macaeme ko lrolrongo ki Kaynoane, kiavaga kaykameane.
english: Teacher, Kaynuane has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

dru: Kanako sia Rathodo Rosodramane, taramangealenga ko cailili kaycaili.
english: My name is Rathudu Rusudramane, and I'm 10 years old.

dru: Soaino so ka zoko ka vavalake?
english: What ethnic group are you from?
Are all your family members indigenous?
Yes, my whole family is Drekay.
Are all your family members indigenous?

dru: Ini, Drekay ko ama, kapairangane ko ina.
english: No, my father is Drekay, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.

dru: Kavay tama so? tarapianga ko caili ini?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

dru: Ini, marodrange ki cekelenay, taramavalrolonga ko caili ini.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

dru: Tarapianga ko caili ki taka ka sawvalay?
Ko kaka ka sawvalay taramangealenga si valro ko caili.
Madraadraw mosoane ko caili ki taka?
english: Is your brother much older than you?
I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

dru: Uono, wamoanganako ki iday si matolrolo kongovenge.

english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

dru: Yakay talangolangodhane, lrikikalromale loasane ka laso.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

dru: Yaino ko Pianiw? lrikikalromale lraboale loasane ka aliso.
english: Where is Pianiw? She's going to compete in a running competition later.

dru: Yakay ki tatolrisisisiane, naw moa daolo iniane.
english: She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

dru: Naw langadhana ko kodrali, loasanenga lrisilapengako mosoane.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

dru: Lo silapa ki droma, lrisilapako ki sinisi.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

dru: Ka Palripilripi lrikikalromale ki wapangolro ki malri kaykameane?
english: Is Palripilripi competing in croquet today?
No, he's competing in high jump.

dru: Loka taongodokadhane lrikipaelre so ki kiakalromale?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?
Will you compete in the sports day?
What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.
Will we sell food at the sports day?

dru: Ini, lrikilangayta ko gomo ka malri.
Wamalra so ko icibange, maparamoro so!
english: Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.
No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

dru: Yakay ki nikay, lo mobelenga silape iniane.
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

dru: Aropo so, maolaynga kaidredreele mosoane, so?
english: It's Arupu. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?
I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.
He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.
She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

dru: Kaiyatavanane ko tomo nomi, yaangaangade, ikayya kay mokalava lomobalriw.
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.
I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.
It's so good to see you.

dru: Kikay abaadhane nomiane ka pangodrale popingisiangana..
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

dru: Maolay kaikelakela, wadaolako mitaane kabalrolo kay aga.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

dru: Palrainga naoongolo ko ocia, tamokadaanane kalaelange.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.
Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

dru: Kikay taocolocoloane kay koko, iloka si ngiabababalay kane.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.

dru: Kiadredreelako mosoane loiya ki miaoaobo ko amadradreelaneta.
english: Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?
How about meeting at school? We need to shoot a video.

dru: Tamoa siwkaiziw kamani midra, lringiragelanako ko Ngodradrekadhane.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

dru: Ngiaesadhane ko sakera ki cekelenay. lokakalapoopoanenga kela silape nakoane.
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!
That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Then come during our Harvest Festival!
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!

dru: Aso kirimo nawsiwlri mobalriw cekecekele iya?
english: May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.
Why not teach in the city?

dru: Mavalringivako ki cekeleli, sidrama ko adolroanli pangibilri ki cekeleli.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

dru: Malrigili so tinono, aneane ko wabolro mosoane?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

dru: Kaingo, amani ko malrilrigilinga ikay ki cekelenay ka taratinono.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.

dru: Aso nao kiborlo ki tatinotinonane iya?
english: How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

dru: Bongokanay kikay watinono, nao paocongolo kay bongoka amiako.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.

dru: Malrigili so toramoro, kikay lripakaolay mado?
english: You're really talented. Does it take a long time to make?

dru: Mathariri ko pataratolro ki dramare pakaango lasangolreeme.
english: It can be left to ferment for up to three months.

dru: Yakay kay kamangolo si kocayli, dokoli patoelre.
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

dru: Paelrelrenga drosa ka iday si malrimale ka balrolane.
Madalamako kikay laimay kay, pia ko paiso?
english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?

dru: Kikay yai lrima ka iday ka balrolane.

english: It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?
No, if I lower it further, I'll lose money.

dru: Iya! lrimalrako ko vaeva ko icecelrenge ko laimay.
english: Alright then, I'll take a black piece of clothing.
I want this knife and this pot.

dru: Paelrelrenga drosa ka kodrolo ka balrolane, kikay ngidadarepeli, masalroako lriarakay mado kaolay.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

dru: Naw pelaelanga ki talragili kela langay, lrimaka paikadoadoay so?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?

dru: Ikatomane! nao kivala ko taydrosane paralobo mosoane.
english: Alright! I'll give you a 20% discount.

dru: Aboala dreela! kialangalangay kay laimay kay talropono.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

dru: Ko vaeva ko laimay tolro ka iday si malrimale, lokatolro kodrolo ka balrolane.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

dru: Lringovaevako langay ala baadhaili ko baavane.
english: I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

dru: Saabaw, nao, langay amiamiako ko coloko si nipokamangolane ka botolo.
english: Hello, I would like to buy sticky rice and braised pork with maqaw pepper.

dru: Pakanaelrenga kilangay ko aga. yakayana kay tana ka tingipora?
english: The rice is sold out. I have tana pancakes, would you like to buy them?

dru: Mathariri, ala baadhaili pakavaevaili, lokabibilrilinga naolangaynga ko aga.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

dru: Mathariri, nao paralobo mosoane polomasane, kikay malrimale ka balrolane.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

dru: sabao makanaelre. kaiasaa aibolroako nomiya ikai akanea ko vaga ki Ngodradrekai tomana loiya.
english: Hello everyone. Today, I'm going to teach you how to say the Rukai word for food.

dru: wathingale so kilalra kai taiya ki singsi?
english: Do you understand what the teacher says?

dru: singsi, kadrowa ka wathingale. aidolro so pela?
english: I don't understand. Can you repeat it again?

dru: kadrowa ka makakyalalra, aidolro so akwadradrao?
english: I can't hear you, can you speak louder?
Look here, please! Repeat after me.
Read it again. Please speak louder.
I forgot to bring my pen.

dru: singsi, mahimoha ko iloko ko sasopisopilra.
english: I forgot to bring my eraser.

dru: kisalroa inya thili so ko sasopisopilra.
english: Please borrow erasers from your classmates.

dru: ta pakeakela ikai, kibolro, ta macecelenga lo pela ki takibolrobolroa.
english: Class dismissed, see you next week.

dru: lalaka ko ki Legeai, sia Sola ko.
english: I am the son of Legeai, and my name is Sula.

dru: sitoa ko ki Koi, sia Sola ko.
english: I am a student in Kui, my name is Sula.

dru: ko nagane ki tamaso sia anea?
ko nagane ki ama sia Legeai.

english: He is my brother, his name is Kecelre.
She is my friend and her name is Kaniyu.

dru: tahapiyanga ko caili ki tama so kaiasaa?
ko ama kaiasaa tahamalrimalenga ka caili.

english: How many brothers and sisters do you have?

dru: yakai ko tadrosa ko kake, tangea ko agi li.
english: I have two brothers and sisters and one younger brother and sister.
How many people are in your family?
There are four of us in our family.

dru: manema ko aonga ki betaka ki tinaso?
english: What does your uncle do for a living?

dru: yakai ko aonga ki taka ka ababai?
english: Does your sister have a job?
Yes, but she is a Paiwan.
Yes, we are all very tall.
Does your sister go to school?
Do your siblings speak the language?
Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
I have three brothers and sisters.

dru: taelre so ki tama so si tina so cekecekele?
english: Do you live with your parents?

dru: eene, taelrea ko ki ama si ina cekecekele.
english: Yes, I live with my mom and dad.

dru: taelre so ki tomo so si kaingo so cekecekele?
english: Do you live with your grandparents?

dru: ini, kadrowa ko ka taelre liniya cekecekele.
english: No, I didn't live with them.

dru: taelrea ko ki ama, ina, si kake ka saowalai cekecekele.
english: I live with my father, mother and brother.

dru: nao alra ko acilai paongolo mosowa.
english: I will bring you some water.

dru: kwanea pangikalra, makalra ko todamai li.
english: Enjoy yourself. I cooked a lot of dishes.
Oh! It smells good and looks delicious.
Enjoy yourself. There is a lot more.
I'll make myself at home then.
Enjoy yourself. There are plenty here.
I ate a lot and couldn't eat any more.
I will take you to the mountains today.

dru: makalra ko atatimalao lregelrege amiya ko ina.
english: Mom says that there are lots of mosquitoes in the mountains.
I will take you to the fields.
Are we going to loosen the soil?
Teacher will take us to the riverside.
Teacher will take us to the mountains today.
Are we going to the riverside today?

dru: ini, aiiloko mita molregelrege kao singsi.
english: No, our teacher is going to take us to the mountains.
Are we going to the mountains today?
No, we are going to the fields.

dru: singsi, aiceele ta ko manema modrakehale?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see at the riverside?
We are going to see dragonflies.

dru: singsi, aiceele ta ko manema molregelrege?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see in the mountains?
We are going to see butterflies.
What are we going to do in the fields?

dru: aiceele ta ko lredreke ta ko lapanai, cwacela ko adradralrele si valo!
english: We are going to see the corn we grow in the fields, but you need to be aware of the ants and bees.
Teacher, are we going to swim in the river?
No, we are going to see dragonflies.

dru: singsi, aimomawma ta lredreke ko lacenge?
english: Teacher, are we going to grow some vegetables in the fields?
We are going to loosen the soil today.

dru: yakai ko takoaiavithi ko ngyapapapalai nakaowai
aitawceela ko ko panyanyaniyake ko takoaiavithi.
english: Today is the first time I see real living dragonflies.

dru: yakai ko alivaevaha ko ngyapapapalai nakaowai.
ye! wa! madalama ko ki alivaevaha, mathahihi!
english: Yeh! Wow! I love butterflies. They are very beautiful.
Those are not butterflies. They are bees.
Come here and take a look. Don't go too far!
Got it, we won't go anywhere too far.

dru: kai lrabwaboale, lwalranga amani lomolrevese nomi.
english: Don't run and walk slowly lest you fall down.
I want to see them right away.
How do you go to the block-house?

dru: waongtinga ko ko didyosa mwa taisolasoladha.

english: How does he go to the hospital?
How do you go to Penghu?

dru: ngwakaiya ko ki hikoki mwa Pengho.
english: I go to Penghu by plane.

dru: ngwakaiya ko ki vahokoho mwa Pengho.
english: I go to Penghu by boat.
How does Muni go to school?

dru: ngwakai ki kisa mogako ko Moni.
english: Muni goes to school by train.
How does Usau go to church?
Usau goes to church by bicycle.
Do you go to school by MRT?
No, I go to school by bus.
Do you go to school by bicycle?
Yes, I go to school by bicycle.
Do you go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail?

dru: eene, ngwakaiya ko ki kaoti moTakao.
english: Yes, I go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail.

dru: lo moTaito so aingokisa so aingohikoki so?
english: Are you going to Taitung by train or by plane?
I will take the plane because it is faster than the train.

dru: lo mokyokai so aingobase so aiongtingi so ko didyosa?
english: Are you going to drive to the church or take the bus?
I will drive to the church because it is more convenient than the bus.
Is the market close to your house?
No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.
Is the post office close to the school?
Yes, it is within walking distance.
Is the restaurant close to the station?

dru: lo molatadra tisaba la dadavace ko gohongkang wakelamado.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.
I would like to visit you.

dru: yakai ko aongane li kaiasaa, pwigaigaa.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

dru: lodhaa aipicogo so? nao silape mosowa lo makamolringedele.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.

dru: eene, nao okalavalava mosowa ikai taowana.
english: Sure, I will wait for you at home.

dru: aimaka royingnga ko? nao topacase amyamiya ko.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

dru: ngyalisiyana ko, la kainako lripethele sooko, anikalisi.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.
Thank you for accepting the interview.

dru: kadrowa ka aikatoma, manema ko nao kitobolro iyaso?
english: You are welcome. What would you like to know?

dru: sa icengecenge so manema ko aongane so?
english: What do you do when you are young?
I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

dru: miyalri ikai cekele ko lalake so?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?
No, my kids are all living in the city.

dru: walapowa ko ko taopongo si adhadhame, miyalri ka wacekecekele li.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

dru: miyalri walapowa ko ko ngyao, lo ikai ko nilapowa kadrowa mado ka masepele.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

dru: apya kitobolrowa ko ko lrisi lo alopo.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

dru: bekela ko thingale li, ai ko tadolrowane li aitobalrea ko mosowa.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.

dru: ko sahakaiyane nomi walopo ka ladreme yakai ko lrisi?
english: Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?

dru: ko sahakaiya walopo ka satwatoma kadrowa ka aimaka hecenge ko labaybai.
english: Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.
Then, can women go hunting together?

dru: ini, kadrowa ka aimaka alopo ko ababai.
english: No, women cannot go hunting either.

dru: Usao, kadrowanga ko bava taowana, mwa lwangai.
english: Usau, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.

dru: yakai tagagaa ko akoeanga, asi langai!
english: There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!

dru: kadrowa ka mwakelrete kwani akoaeaea, mwana lwangai ko akoadrosa.
english: One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

dru: ailangadha ko ko bava, kyalangalangai nomi?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?
Yes! How many bottles do you need?

dru: aipakodrosa ko, lai langaiyanana ko ko akoaea ko pagai.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.

dru: kaivai pagai, manemaneana ko alangadhane so?
english: Here is the rice, what else do you need?

dru: ailangaiyanana ko ko batoko, yakai nomiya?
english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

dru: ailangadha ko ko ngengetele ko alrimaa.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.
Please give me the clothes in blue.

dru: Usao, amwa so ino koasaa? waongdo so?
english: Usau, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

dru: ini, palribola ko ki kaingo lwangai ko lacenge.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

dru: iya! aipicogo so lomaongo? nai kahedele ta kwane ko aga.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?
No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

dru: sabao, piya ko salangadha ikai lacenge?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?
The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?
Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

dru: bwaadhai li ko drosa ka taeheca ko lacenge si ea ka tingitingi ko bohasi.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

dru: Usao, mahimoha ko ko cingpi, aimaka pakisalro so nakowa?
english: Usau, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

dru: miyalriya ko kai iloko, yaki Moni kaivai.
english: I don't have one either. This is Muni's.

dru: aimaka pakisalro so nakowa padalro? aisaha saolriya ko mosowa.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.
Thank you and thank Muni for me.

dru: aisaolriya ko ikai drosa ka hongo.
english: I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?

dru: aikisalrowanana ko ikai tolro ka hongo.
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

dru: eene, ngolringava swaolri lo makatolrolonga ko vai.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

dru: kadrowa so ka wasaolriyana nakowa idra sasopisopilra.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.
Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to Usau?
I don't know. I will go and ask her.

dru: nao pakisalrowana mosowa ikai sasopisopilrane li.
english: I will lend you my eraser first.

dru: Moni, kaivai ebele pakisalro mosawa ki Usao?
english: Muni, did Usau lend you this coat?

dru: ini, langai ki ina bwaai nakowa.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

dru: kodra ebele ki Usao mahahamao inya yaso.
english: Usau's coat is the same as yours.

dru: icecelrenge kodra ebele ini, makakaela ko kolao.
english: His coat is black, so our colors are different.

dru: Moni, kyasalro so ki Usao ko paiso?
english: Muni, did you borrow money from Usau?

dru: eene, nao saolri kaiasaa amiya ko, mahimoha ko kai iloko ko paiso.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.

dru: eene, nao palribolonga mosowa pelaela ki Usao.
english: Okay, I will tell Usau for you.

dru: kai tolriki ahakai mado ko taenge, kai tikohai ahakai mado ko nipalrea, lomiyainiya pacengecenge.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

dru: lanika myaiyainiya, pasalrisalriva ko, thahepana ko kai makapwalralra.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

dru: lobibilrili nao bolronga mosowa dwahepe ikaivai taidrosaa ka tokolro.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

dru: eene, alamatiyakihagai! lobibilrili aidolrongana ko pwalra ko pana.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

dru: madrawnga ko obolo omawma, mwa sooko malra ko kolringi, la ta momawma.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

dru: yathiili ki hevehe, sana modaane so ki sooko aiceele so.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

dru: cwaceela, amanilo kadola so, mahangisi kodra kolringi.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

dru: yakai inya lebe ki angato ko tokolro li.
english: My trap is under that tree.

dru: yakai ko sapatothingalane li, wathingala ko ko taikaiya idra tokolro li.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

dru: kaivai ka thalidoko, pyakai nai ki drakehale si tokaange.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

dru: kadrowa ko thalidoko ikai talikai nai, ahakai nai ko lalikilika tokaange.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

dru: kadrowanaka ahakaiyana ko lalikilika lrwakoili, bolrowai li lobibilrili?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?
Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

dru: nao bolronga mosowa lobibilrili dwahepe ko thalidoko.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

dru: ngyavelevele kwani lalikilikane so, asi ikai ko kaange ko kyakaili! lrwabwala bilibili.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

dru: drengehana, malaliyokai kaivai vahokoho. nao ikai ikaivai bilibili inya lalikilika, mwa nakaowai malra idra lravathe.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

dru: bilibila papiya nakowa inya kaange, nao palribolo mosowa bilibili.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

dru: alamaesai! savaiyane ta kaiasaa, syaetenga ki homoko.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.

dru: ila ta saha obalriyo pakisopilri ki sakacekele ta.
english: Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.
Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

dru: kayasaa singci lrima, lodhaa taibalriva, ilata kahedele avavaehe!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

dru: lodhaa singci tolro, lo makamolringedele lodhaa ilata ngimaimalri!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!
What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

dru: lodha niciyobi, aikahedelako ki ina mokyokai.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.
Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.
May I go wash my hands?
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

dru: singsi, waangeange kay aolroli, aiibalrivako lomyaiyaobo.
english: Teacher, I have a severe headache. I need to take a sick leave in the afternoon.
Okay, take care and go home.

dru: singsi, lobibilrili ki singci ea aiibalrivako, aikiceelako ki kwisang.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.
She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

dru: singsi, ko Koi kyaangeange ki cilolra, aiibalriyo kayasaa.
english: Teacher, Kui has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

dru: sya Solako, kay caili kay tahamangealenga ko cailili.
english: My name is Sulaku, and I'm 10 years old.
What ethnic group are you from?
Are all your family members indigenous?

dru: eene, konai ka wacekecekele Ngodradrekainai makanaelre.
english: Yes, my whole family is Rukai.

dru: ini, ko ama Ngodradrekai, ko ina paihange.
english: No, my father is Rukai, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.
Is that your father? How old is he?
Is that your father? How old is he?

dru: ini, mahodrange ki cekelenai, tahamavalrolonga ko cailini.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

dru: tahapiyanga ko caili ki taka ka saowalai?
ko kake ka saowalai tahamangealenga si valro ko cailini.
ko taka ka saowalai ko cailini takataka mosowa ko makalra?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

dru: ko elrenganeli idai si masopatele ka konghweng.
maolaingata kai macaceele, aso myaki wasowainga kaelrenge?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

dru: eene, konako idainga si matolrolo ka konghweng ko elrenganeli.

english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

dru: yakai talawlawlangodha, loasaa aikipaelre ki makalrwalrmale ki lawlangoi.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

dru: yakai ino ko Moni? aikikalromale ki laylai loasaa.
english: Where is Muni? She's going to compete in a running competition later.
She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

dru: nao lanagaiyana ko kwalre, loasaa naokelanga silape mosowa.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

dru: silapa ko droma, aisilapako ki singsi.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

dru: ko Koi kayasaa aikikalromale ki wadrodromolro ki malri?
english: Is Kui competing in croquet today?
No, he's competing in high jump.

dru: lo atalrabwabwala idra vayvai yakai ko akipaelreaneso?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?
What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.
Will we sell food at the sports day?
Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.
No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.
He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

dru: lanika Sola, maolaingata kaiceele mosowa. mwadringadringaiso?
english: It's Sula. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?
I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.
He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.
She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

dru: kadrowa ko tomonomi, yakai omawma, ikaiya taowana wadradrao iniya.
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.
I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.
It's so good to see you.

dru: kaivai abadha nomiya ka pangodrale, podringadha pikai ki pingsyang.
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

dru: ani kaikelakela, nao daolowana anikela kwane ikay aga.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

dru: aikatoma, sana ongolako ikay ociya makakelrete, taikai zimoso kalaelaelange.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.
Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

dru: nicolocolowa kay tahokoko, iloka si ngilalalalrange kwane.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.

dru: nao ila mosowa lo makamolringedele lodhaa ene?
english: Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?
How about meeting at school? We need to shoot a video.

dru: taikai hahobowa amani, tasikahingalai ko kacalrilrisiyana.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

dru: ko sakera ki cekelenai longipaipai maela ki thahihi. lo ngipaipainga pohana kelangaili silape.
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!

dru: laikaita mokalava pakela ki kalahyahiga, kai ngyalalrange tohamoho!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Then come during our Harvest Festival!
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!
May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.
Why not teach in the city?

dru: mabahengehako ki cekeleli, lasidramako ko apangibilriya ki cekele.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

dru: malrigiliso tinono, anea ko wabolro mosowa?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

dru: amani ko kaingo, amani ko malrilrigilinga tinono ki cekelenai.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.
How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

dru: kay watinono kakoakodhaneta, apya pacongolako ikay kakoakodhaneta.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.
You're really talented. Does it take a long time to make?

dru: ini, aimakapitolo. wasalengemado ko becenge si toboongo, lathalre pakamamelre, lopoliyonga paowa ki dilrongo, la paowanga ko bae.
english: No, it only takes about a week. Pound the hulled millet into flour after soaking it in water, stir it until it thickens, put it into an urn and add red quinoa powder to it.

dru: yakai kay tavangolo si rakyo, ngilralredrekeli demedeme.
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

dru: elrelree drosa ka idai si malrimale.

english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?
It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?
No, if I lower it further, I'll lose money.
Alright then, I'll take a black piece of clothing.
I want this knife and this pot.

dru: elrelre drosa ka kodrolo, ngikakamanili ahaalrima dwahepe, aitaha kaolaiso ahakai.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

dru: lo syokadhako ko talrailragili kela lwangai, aidolroso topadolro?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?

dru: eene! naotopadolro ko sopate ka idai.
english: Alright! I'll give you a 20% discount.

dru: nyama ceela! yakai kay talropono si kahingalai kay akilangadha.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

dru: ko ea tolro ka idai si malrimale, lo ngotolroa kodrolo.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.
I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

dru: sabao, ailangadhako ko dohai ka aga si niceheba ki makao ka beate.
english: Hello, I would like to buy sticky rice and braised pork with maqaw pepper.

dru: kadrowanga ko aga. yakaiyana kay nipaibowa ki tana ka tingpera ailangaiso?
english: The rice is sold out. I have tana pancakes, would you like to buy them?

dru: eene, bwadhaili pakaea, lobibilrili naokelanga lwangai ko aga.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

dru: eene, tanao cabo, kayvai malrimale ka balrola.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

dru: ipoingaw nyamo. sesane ki singsi ka paigo'o amimitiya na akanakanane na wathakongadavadavanane.
english: Hello everyone. Today, I am going to teach you how to say food in thakongadavane.

dru: waigo'o nyaso, biciingi bakaini ki singsi.
english: Do you understand what the teacher says?
I don't understand. Can you repeat it again?
I can't hear you, can you speak louder?

dru: cengela nakay! kisa'apaa nakoa wasyasipi kovasale.
english: Look here, please! Repeat after me.
Read it again. Please speak louder.
I forgot to bring my pen.

dru: singsi, maymoo kake wameca na sadrisidrisi.
english: I forgot to bring my eraser.
Please borrow erasers from your classmates.

dru: tapata'athay nakay solate, tapacengecengele no saka'isekangenga.
english: Class dismissed, see you next week.

dru: kake ka valakini ki Gilagilaw. Tanobake kake.
english: I am the son of Gilagilaw, and my name is Tanobake.

dru: kake ka siitoini ki Gilagilaw. Tanobake kake.
english: I am a student in Gilagilaw, and my name is Tanobake.

dru: acini ki tatavi nakoa ka Gilagilaw.
kini ka kaka nakoa, acini ka Masegesege.
english: He is my brother, his name is Masegesege.

dru: acini ka 'Ipolo. kini ka titini nakoa.
kini ka lalili, acini ka Dredrase.
english: She's a friend of mine, and her name is Dredrase.

dru: nakay cicavili ka watamangesalenga sika drosa na cavilini
tatavi mosoa ka watapiyaninga na cavilini nakay cicavili.
nakay cicavili ka watamaimalenga na cavilini ki tatavi nakoa.

english: How many brothers and sisters do you have?

dru: 'iyakay nakoa 'adrosa na kaka, si la'asaseane na gili.
english: I have two brothers and sisters and one younger brother and sister.
How many people are in your family?
There are four of us in our family.

dru: tatavi mosoa ka manini ko kamolini?
english: What does your uncle do for a living?

dru: kaki mosoa ka 'iyakay nyani na kamolini?
english: Does your sister have a job?

dru: kidro drodrosa cocoaw ka ma'alamengane nyani?
esi, ma'aagae kiname maesale ka thakada'ane.
english: Yes, we are all very tall.
Does your sister go to school?

dru: gili mosoa ka waigo'o nyani thoakongadangadavane.
english: Do your siblings speak the language?
Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
How many brothers and sisters do you have?
I have three brothers and sisters.
Do you live with your parents?

dru: e'e, 'iyaese kiname ki tatava si titina.

Wow! The corn tastes so sweet.

dru: idoo kake kane na athiwko, kamani kane na lrin-go.
english: I can't eat oranges. I will have some apples instead.
Sure, I like it very much.

dru: ko kathape na madro laso kane.
english: Let me peel the fruit for you.
Thank you. This fruit is so juicy.

dru: ko alra na acilay pa'ongolo mosoa.
english: I will bring you some water.
Enjoy yourself. I cooked a lot of dishes.
Oh! It smells good and looks delicious.
Enjoy yourself. There is a lot more.
I'll make myself at home then.
Enjoy yourself. There are plenty here.
I ate a lot and couldn't eat any more.

dru: sesane ka ameameceami mwane ki singsi mwa egeege.
english: I will take you to the mountains today.

dru: egeege ka 'iyakay madraw na atatinga'olo ami ki titina.
english: Mom says that there are lots of mosquitoes in the mountains.

dru: sesane ka ameameceami mwane ki singsi mwa tawmoma.
english: I will take you to the fields.
Are we going to loosen the soil?

dru: singsi ka ameameceami mitiya mwa drakeale.
english: Teacher will take us to the riverside.

dru: singsi ka ameameceami mitiya mwa egeege.
english: Teacher will take us to the mountains today.
Are we going to the riverside today?

dru: 'aini, ameameceami mitiya ki singsi mwa egeege.
english: No, our teacher is going to take us to the mountains.
Are we going to the mountains today?
No, we are going to the fields.

dru: singsi, mwata drakeale ka mani ko cengeleyanita?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see at the riverside?
We are going to see dragonflies.

dru: singsi, mwata egeege ka mani ko cengeleyanita?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see in the mountains?
We are going to see butterflies.
What are we going to do in the fields?

dru: wamikita tawmoma cengele ko sadoko'ita ngodrangodro, cengela 'iyakay na abongo'o si valo.
english: We are going to see the corn we grow in the fields, but you need to be aware of the ants and bees.
Teacher, are we going to swim in the river?
No, we are going to see dragonflies.

dru: singsi, waminiata tawmoma doko'o na lacenge?
english: Teacher, are we going to grow some vegetables in the fields?
We are going to loosen the soil today.

dru: sesane ka ta'ocengelela kake na mawdripi na apopangoo.
english: Today is the first time I see real living dragonflies.

dru: wa! madalame kake na acale, maagi'i swakoa.
english: Yeh! Wow! I love butterflies. They are very beautiful.

dru: kini ka i'aacale, kini ka valo.
english: Those are not butterflies. They are bees.

dru: 'ikaya nakay cengele, adriowa na ma'adavili na dida'ane.
english: Come here and take a look. Don't go too far!

dru: e'e, waiya kiname na ma'adavili na dida'ane.
english: Got it, we won't go anywhere too far.
Don't run and walk slowly lest you fall down.
I want to see them right away.
How do you go to the block-house?

dru: wa'engtingi kake na sangepae mwa ta'oanane.

english: How does he go to the hospital?
How do you go to Penghu?
I go to Penghu by plane.
I go to Penghu by boat.

dru: Tangooco ka mani 'inonini no mwani kiwkay?
english: How does Tangooco go to church?
Tangooco goes to church by bicycle.
Do you go to school by MRT?
No, I go to school by bus.
Do you go to school by bicycle?
Yes, I go to school by bicycle.
Do you go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail?

dru: esi, 'iyanono kake na kaw-tyi mwa Takao.
english: Yes, I go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail.
Are you going to Taitung by train or by plane?

dru: 'angohikoki kake, 'angohikokimade ka maidai kimade na kisya.
english: I will take the plane because it is faster than the train.

dru: mwaso kiwkay ka 'angobase nyaso? wa'engetingi nyaso na sangepae?
english: Are you going to drive to the church or take the bus?

dru: wa'engtingi kake na sangepae, 'engtingimade na sangepae ka maidai kimade na base.
english: I will drive to the church because it is more convenient than the bus.
Is the market close to your house?
No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.
Is the post office close to the school?
Yes, it is within walking distance.

dru: takanakanane na do'o ka wade'ethe nyani tisyaba?
english: Is the restaurant close to the station?

dru: mobalatimade tisyaba ka wadavadavace kimade 'aima na penkang lakela.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.
I would like to visit you.

dru: 'iyakay ko dwapili sesane i'ikay kake da'ane. saka va'iyanane.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

dru: 'amao nyaso nosi'a? ko 'awkay no viva'ane nga silape mosoa.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.
Sure, I will wait for you at home.

dru: amiyani doomyali lwigi? ko solate sobili.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

dru: ikaagi'i na ta'acoavanili, soko ka isenekete, 'ayni.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.
Thank you for accepting the interview.
You are welcome. What would you like to know?

dru: kokiboboli mosoa ko 'icengecengiso ka mani paythayiso?
english: What do you do when you are young?

dru: kisace kake ko booane, makasi 'iyasasadranga kake.
english: I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

dru: kokibobolimosoa valakiso ka syada'ane nyane 'ikay tacekecekelane?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?
No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

dru: wathade'e kake 'angisea na atho si 'angisea na alralrame, thakada'anili.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

dru: wathade'e kake 'angisea na ngiyaoo, silangelange na thade'imade.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

dru: 'api kiboboo kake mosoa na walopimade na kaisyane.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

dru: ikadraw na igo'ili, makasi igo'ili 'akobi ka no 'akobii mekake mosoa.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.
Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?
Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.
Then, can women go hunting together?
No, women cannot go hunting either.

dru: 'Ase, kadrowa da'ane na bava, mwa langay na bava.
english: Kacaw, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.
There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!

dru: sesane ka iebate, mwa la lwangay 'angidrosa.
english: One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

dru: no langay mikake na bava, 'iyakay nyani?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?
Yes! How many bottles do you need?

dru: no lwangay mekake 'angidrosa, la langay la 'angisea na be'ase.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.

dru: be'ase ka 'iyakay nakay, mani langayaniso laa?
english: Here is the rice, what else do you need?

dru: no langay laa mekake na bawthotho, 'iyakay nyani?
english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

dru: langay mekake na maekekene taymane na kopingi.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.
Please give me the clothes in blue.
kacaw, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

dru: 'aini, amwa kake pasopaa takawngane lwangay na lacenge.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

dru: aminyani nyane, 'amao nyaso na ma'awbo? wamyata 'angese kwane na do'o?
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?
No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

dru: ipoingaw nyaso, kokiboolimosoa kikay lelacenge ka piyani na payso?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

dru: sesane na lacenge ka maposale na payso.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.

dru: kikay bwathi ka piyani na payso?
english: How much are these sweet potatoes?

dru: bwathi ka sesane tingatingi ka matoolo na payso
english: Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

dru: bwa'a koa 'angidosa na lacenge si sesane tingatingi na bwathi.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

dru: 'Ase, maymoo kake wamece na sasolasolate, doo myaso pasodame nakoa?
english: kacaw, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

dru: kadrowa koa, kikay ka yaini ki Momoni.
english: I don't have one either. This is Momoni's.

dru: doo myaso pasodame koa padodaw'o, dodaw'o mekake swavivi mosoa.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.
Thank you and thank Panay for me.

dru: no savivi mekake nakay drodrosa na solate.
english: I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?
I would like to borrow these three books.
Sure and remember to return them after three days.
You haven't returned me the eraser.
Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to kacaw?

dru: iigo'o kake, ko wa kiboboo nyane.
english: I don't know. I will go and ask her.
I will lend you my eraser first.

dru: Momoni, kikay ebele ka pasodamini nyani mosoa ki 'Ase?
english: panay, did kacaw lend you this coat?

dru: 'aini, kikay ka langaini koa ki titina.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.
kacaw's coat is the same as yours.
His coat is black, so our colors are different.
panay, did you borrow money from kacaw?

dru: e'e, ko savivi mekake sesane, la kaymoo ka wamece na payso.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.
Okay, I will tell kacaw for you.

dru: tamothoane ka syakay kimade na ta'ene pwalra tiko'ase ka syakay kimade na athii pwalra, myani nyane ka tyakadringay.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.
No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

dru: si ko paigo'o mosoa, yamimade paithay na sa the'ee si ta'ene.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

dru: e'e! maagi'i sawkoa! nomyani nyane ka biilanenga ka alramikake na bee.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

dru: tawmoma sosoao ka mathangeda'a, mwa soko malra na sa'alodro, tawwa tawmoma.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

dru: 'iyakay ongolo cigi'ane, moda'aniso sooko ka cengele mikoso.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

dru: cengela, macongavanga koso, sa'alodro ka magaange.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.
My trap is under that tree.

dru: pwakalava kake pa'ikay nakay, waigo'o kake ta'ikanini athiili.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

dru: kikay omoko ka pa'ikay kiname drakeale poomoko.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

dru: namiya ka kadrowa na omoko, syakay kiname na thanagipane nwagipi.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

dru: isyakay la kake na nagipi, piilanenga ka paigo'o nikoso nakoa?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?

dru: e'e! nobiilanenga ka ta'angeese mwa nwaginagipi.
english: Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.
I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

dru: 'avelevele nagipiso, mwanagipinga nyani na ka'ange, ibonga bilibili.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

dru: adralala, aavange ka 'avelevele. ko'ikay nakay bilibili, mwaladroway malra na tala'ethe.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

dru: bilibila kaka'ange pawanakay. kopasopaa mosoa bilibili.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

dru: maagi'i sawkoa! madraw aitasesane, sya'etenga omoko.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.
Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.
Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

dru: nosi'a ka watato na va'iyane, nosi'a noviva'anenga ka tawwa 'aangi na malri!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!
What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

dru: nosi'a ka niciyobi, no'angese mikake ki titini nakowa mwa kyokai.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.
Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.
May I go wash my hands?
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

dru: singsi, wa'ange'ange na aoili, na viva'anenga ka nosika mikake.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

dru: singsi 'ano sakasokobanenga ka nosika mikake, nowa mikake kicengele na koisanhe.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.
